  "body": "**Problem:**\r\nUsing await in a test will print the `    Warning: An update to App inside a test was not wrapped in act(...).` warning.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nimport React from 'react';\r\nimport { render } from 'react-testing-library'\r\nimport { act } from 'react-dom/test-utils'\r\nimport App from './App';\r\nimport sleep from 'sleep-promise'\r\n\r\nit('increments click count', async () => {\r\n  let container, getByText\r\n\r\n  act(() => {\r\n   ({container, getByText} = render(<App />))\r\n   getByText('Click me').click()\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  await sleep(1000) // this line causes the error to be printed\r\n  expect(container.textContent).toMatch('1')\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected result:**\r\n\r\nThe warning should not appear in cases like this.\r\n",
